"The price of a single bitcoin hit $10,000 for the first time since the beginning of the month, underscoring a rally in the world's No. 1 cryptocurrency since touching a recent low. Bitcoin has risen about 68% since touching a low below $6,000, according to news and research site CoinDesk. Bitcoin BTCUSD, +9.77% hit an intraday high of $10,064.98, representing a 5.6% increase on the day, dragging other major digital currencies along for the uptrend. That said, the virtual currency is still below its late-December peak at around $20,000.\n\nRead the full story: Bitcoin rises back above $10,000 as rally continues"